Loan Data from Prosper¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others. Data dictionary to understand the variables more form this link: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1gDyi_L4UvIrLTEC6Wri5nbaMmkGmLQBk-Yx3z0XDEtI/edit#gid=0

Here is some questions We are trying to answer:¶

What factors affect a loan’s outcome status?¶

What affects the borrower’s APR or interest rate?¶

Are there differences between loans depending on how large the original loan amount was?¶

Prosper Loan Data - important Variable Definitions:¶
  • ListingCreationDate : The date the listing was created.
  • CreditGrade : The Credit rating that was assigned at the time the listing went live. Applicable for listings pre-2009 period and will only be populated for those listings.
  • Term : The length of the loan expressed in months.
  • BorrowerAPR : The Borrower's Annual Percentage Rate (APR) for the loan.
  • BorrowerRate : The Borrower's interest rate for this loan.
  • LenderYield : The Lender yield on the loan. Lender yield is equal to the interest rate on the loan less the servicing fee.
  • ProsperScore : A custom risk score built using historical Prosper data. The score ranges from 1-10, with 10 being the best, or lowest risk score. Applicable for loans originated after July 2009.
  • ProsperRating (Alpha) : The Prosper Rating assigned at the time the listing was created between AA - HR. Applicable for loans originated after July 2009.
  • CreditScoreRangeLower : The lower value representing the range of the borrower's credit score as provided by a consumer credit rating agency.The lower value representing the range of the borrower's credit score as provided by a consumer credit rating agency.
  • LoanOriginationDate: The date the loan was originated.

The current status indicates the current status of the loan: Cancelled, Chargedoff, Completed, Current, Defaulted, FinalPaymentInProgress, PastDue. The PastDue status will be accompanied by a delinquency bucket.

As we can see from the Bar Chart that the number of completed loans in our data set is the second higher number after current, which reflects that most of the clients that requested a loan are able to complete it.

IncomeRange indicates The income range of the borrower at the time the listing was created.

As we can see from the Bar Chart that the people with Income Range from $25,000 to 74,999 are the ones who are taking loans most

BorrowerRate indicates The Borrower's interest rate for this loan.

As we ca see from the histogram that the Interest Rate in our data set is normally distributed with the peak between 14 and 18 percent in addition we have some increase in the 35 percent

BorrowerAPR indicates The Borrower's Annual Percentage Rate (APR) for the loan.

As we can see from the histogram that the Inetrest Rate in our data set is normally distrubuted with the peak between 15 and 20 percent, As we can see peak of APR higher than Intrest rate peak that is because the APR includes not only the interest expense on the loan but also all fees and other costs involved in procuring the loan.
